    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-08T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20235/2–846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-08T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >February 8, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 8—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>415. <gloss target="#t_reEmbtel1">ReEmbtel</gloss> 403, February 6, 9 p.m.,<note
                        n="43" xml:id="d164fn43">Not printed.</note> and <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 160, January 26, 2 p.m. I believe that Cooke is making real
                    effort to get as many Nazi agents as he can off on <hi rend="italic">Highland
                        Monarch</hi>. There appears good reason to suppose that Cooke is genuinely
                    concerned at what we may do and reveal, and that the principal obstacles are
                    anti-Perón courts dominated by conservatives which are looking with decidedly
                    jaundiced eye on war as well as other powers revolutionary Government has sought
                    to arrogate to itself.</p>
                <pb facs="0219" n="201" xml:id="pg_201"/>
                <p>Under circumstances I doubt that drastic action or recriminations would be
                    justified on basis of failure to deliver agents under court order. Freude<note
                        n="44" xml:id="d164fn44">Ludwig Freude, German-born head of Cía General de
                        Construcciones, accused of espionage in behalf of the Axis.</note> case is
                    in somewhat different category despite fact Court of Appeals has cleared way for
                    securing Argentine citizenship. Naturally if Government fails to deport any
                    agents not under court order my recommendation does not apply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
